<td><a href="UltraBoard.cgi?Action=ShowProfile&ID=dalass&Board=general&Idle=30&Sort=0&Order=Descend&Page=2&Session=" target="Profile" OnMouseOver="window.status='View Dalass (dalass) Profile.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Profile</font></a></td><td align="RIGHT"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">What is the deal with beggars anyways?  I personaly have never begged and have worked very hard for what I have and for someone to try to persistantly beg me for my items (which I need to stay alive) make me very angry.  I am especialy miffed by those who beg for what I am equiped with.  And unfortunantly most beggars don't get the point when I say NO NO NO! ! !   Why am I going to spend 200pp on my axe and then hand it over to a beggar so I can be wepon-less? And why is it that people feel the need to beg?  The thing that angers me the most is when someone is begging me and and I don't realy have time to play the begging game, (you know where you say no, and they become more persistant.) All I want to do is to tell this person to get F#c#ed, but it makes me feel like a total D#ck.  I apologize for going off, but for those of you who read this and ARE beggars, why don't you spend more time earning your money and gaining exp instead of wasting other players limited playing time and agravating them.  I donate what I can to those who need it.  I try to help folks out when I can, but I will NOT help a beggar.  I just don't like feeling awkward when all I want to do is play and have fun.  Money doesn't come easy, but if you work hard it will come.  Take the time to enjoy the game. Thanks for listening. :)<hr>Dalass Daniels (Norrath Guardians of Honor)<br>
Warrior of the 40th Blade<br>
*Tribunal*</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
