<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Since you obviously just needed to vent, I'll refrain from my usual wiseass response (and a dozen of them popped up while I was typing this sentence). Feel my pain.<p>

Seriously, this is a valid point. Asking for a hand is one thing, begging for pp, armor, buffs, etc. is just annoying. Every character starts as a naked newbie. Eventually every character can become a buff and bad-ass lv. 50 mob-masher. Granted, at the start the leveling and equipping process may seem daunting, but its obviously doable. For Tunare's sake, people, show some pride!<p>

And why Verant saw fit to include a Beg skill is beyond me (first person to say "realism" gets backstabbed!).<p>

Corax, Wood Elf Rogue<br>
