<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Tell you guys the truth, I sometimes ask for handouts myself, no, I don't go around, bothing people with tells, nagging em, etc etc, but instead, send a friendly OOC to the zone I'm in, asking if anyone has anything they would like to give kindly to a level 1 newbie.  I dont get tells telling me to shut my trap, or put a sock in it, or do it yourself, etc.  Instead, either someone sends me a tell saying that they had somethin for me, or, nobody answers, and I bet the reason that is is because I probably play on a nicer server(s).  When I was playing my higher level, and find rusty weaps, i usually hand em out to a newbie, and then about 3 min afterward keep an eye on em to see if they do well with it or want to give it back, (rarely).  I was glad i stayed once though, I was with a young man, forgot his name, wood elf newbie, warrior, in greater Faydark, on my way to sell after I jst had exited Crushbone, (you know how encumbered you egt when you finally leave there to sell, especially if you have 8 packs full.)  Anyway, he was fighting a widom spiderling hatchling, which he forgot to con, and was a level higher than him, i suspected, the spider was winning, i lent a hand, 2 blows with my minotaur battle axe sent it down, he thanked me looted itr, and i offered to let him group with me so my healing song would effect him, he agreed.  Shortly after, i gave him a rusty scythe, a rusty spear, and a rusty battle axe to get him started.  I was abou to leave, we were both full health...  when an orc centurion came from around the corner.  I saved the lad just in time, he was half way gone with his purple bar by the time i slayed it.  He thanked me again, i returned him to full health, i left, tat was that.  The point im making with that story is that hgiher levels should keep an eye out for newbies, cause there bare skin aint gonna protect them from much.  I'm trying to say that if a n ewbie asks for some armor or other item in OOC, just dont answer it if you dont want to, or, give him something, not yell shouts at him caling him a lazy bum who should get off his ass and do some real work for a change.  If he sends you a tell, asking for something, just say no, but, if he follows you or spams you, THEN yell the heck outta him.  In fact, I LIKE rude newbies like that yelled at, but the point I'm making is, don't yell at a newbie kindly asking for something spare, yell at em if they keep on inspecting you after you told em not to, or they are sending tell after tell at you.  I do NOT accuse anyone here about their reactions and thoughts, I'm just saying things from my own point of view, and yes, I know that feeling when a newbie keeps sending tells at ya, been there. (In my opinion, I don't know why people don't like being inspected, is there an extra armor slot we have yet to see?).  Well, thats my opinin, and please do not take it the wrong way.<br>
Wisdom Wizard</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
