<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">A little story, laugh if you will, flame if you must.<p>

While playing My SK in Qeynos I was given a tell by a 1st level SK asking where the guild was, I replied for him to meet me at the bank and I'd show him. While a low level warrior comes in, did not do a /who but seem to remember "her" being about 4th, She asks for 4pp, I say I don't have 4pp (a lie, after cashing up I actually had 5!!!) and even if I did I do not give to beggars. She uses the /grin emote and I leave the bank to wait outside, while there I here ask the other character in the bank for 2pp. The new SK arrives and I start to lead him under the arena to the SK entrance, the beggar is following. I carry on, stopping to wait for the other SK occasionally and realise the beggar is still following, I start to checking behind me now, not only to make sure that the SK is behind me but to ensure the beggar can follow. Any of you that haven't guessed, this other character is going to be KoS in the SK/Nec guild and doesn't stand a chance. <br>
Was I out of order doing this? Yes, probably but I was playing an evil character...saying that had she not begged I would have made vieled threats to ward them off, still it was cruel.<br>
Did I get satisfaction or pleasure from doing this? You betcha life I did.<p>

Last note.. my SK is twinked, nothing major (I can't afford much) but twinked all the same.<br>
When the 1st level SK had completed their business I gave him my spare leather armour and an SBH.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
