<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I have only asked for money once when I started EQ, and that was after i did some fighting of my own and quickly caught on to one simple newbie fact: More space means more loot (off the stuff i kill) and so i did some shopping and found how much i needed to get me started. I asked a 30+ person for exactly 2pp so i could buy some backpacks, and that was that. Since then I have gotten my char to 37 and have had a great time.However, ive never had to deal with any beggars, probably because im one scary mofo Shadowknight decked out in full DF (quested every piece myself). To add to the look, i now carry charred armor and an opaline helm for non-combat situations, and and the complete black look really doesnt attract many beggars, and perhaps the horns on my skull shaped helms (as a DE) adds a little effect too =)<p>

The moral of the story: After doing my homework, i did fine with a li'l cash, and never asked for armor or weapons, cause thats simply unneccessary.A few backpacks to hold yer loot, and the rest is history. Wise up and you too can be successful, without begging for handouts for a living--besides, you dont level while sitting at a zone spending your time bothering ppl.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
