<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">My opinion on begging (as if anyone cares):<br>
When I go into cities during peak hours I often get up to 10 tells asking for stuff.  I find it very annoying when I am having conversations with other people.  In my opinion if you've played long enough to look up peoples names and send them tells begging you should know how to go and hunt for a few GP yourself.  One thing I don't mind is if you roleplay a begger.  If it fits your character and you play it well thats fine.  But sending /tell messages isn't roleplaying.  What I say to beggers is "What?  You are going to give me plat?"  Or something along those lines.  I just make them think I don't understand and hopefully frustrate them as much as they frustrate us sometimes.  Hey you know someone will give them something sometime so they might as well go through a little trying to get it.  And to the Sk who led the begger into the KOS area that was pretty mean.  But funny in a crule sort of way.  If they wandered in there they probably were a true newbie.  And you should have just told them it's rude to beg...<p>

My 2cp</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
